{/* HERO */}

How to Activate Your License

New to real estate or returning to active status? Follow these steps to meet Nevada requirements, associate with ARAD, and start working with modern digital tools.

{/* QUICK PATHS */}

New Licensee

Complete pre-license education, pass the state exam, fingerprint/background, apply to the Division, and associate with ARAD to activate.

Reactivating

If your license is inactive, update fingerprints if needed, file the Division forms, and associate with ARAD to return to active status.

Transferring In

Coming from another brokerage? We’ll prep the transfer paperwork and coordinate timing around any pending transactions.

{/* STEPS + CHECKLIST */}

Step-by-Step

  1. Education. Complete the Nevada pre-license course through an approved provider.
  2. Exam. Schedule and pass the national & state portions with the testing provider. Keep your score report.
  3. Fingerprints & Background. Submit fingerprints through an approved vendor.
  4. Apply with the Division. File your application and fees with the Nevada Real Estate Division (include score report & fingerprint receipt).
  5. Associate with ARAD. Choose non-MLS practice, referral-only, or partner-MLS. We’ll provide brokerage forms and DocuSign to finalize association.
  6. Post-Licensing / CE. Track required courses after activation to stay compliant.
Need help choosing a path? We’ll help you decide between non-MLS practice, referral-only, or partnering with an MLS agent when needed.

What You’ll Need

  • Government ID
  • Pre-license course certificates
  • Exam score report
  • Fingerprint/background receipt
  • Completed NV RED application & fees
  • Brokerage association docs (ARAD via DocuSign)
Join ARAD Ask a Question
{/* TIMELINE + COST SNAPSHOT */}

Typical Timeline

  • 1–4 weeks Pre-license education (self-paced)
  • 1–2 weeks Exam scheduling & testing
  • 3–10 days Fingerprints & background posted
  • 3–10 days Division application processing
  • Same day ARAD association via DocuSign

Times vary by provider, testing availability, and state processing volume.

Cost Snapshot (estimate)

  • Pre-license course
  • Exam & retake fees (if needed)
  • Fingerprints / background
  • State application / licensing fees
  • ARAD plan (non-MLS or referral-only)

Exact amounts depend on providers and the plan you choose with ARAD.

{/* RESOURCES */}

Helpful Resources

Nevada Real Estate Division – applications & FAQs Schedule/prepare for your exam (testing provider) Fingerprinting locations & appointments SilverFlume – Nevada business licensing portal

ARAD does not provide legal advice. Please consult the Nevada Real Estate Division and Secretary of State for current requirements and fees.
